_header: Our ship is launched from the ground
_description: ‘De Navi vel Puppe. A.D. 1458’, political verses on the State by a Lancastrian — two 4-line stanzas (aaab) plus burden (b): ‘Stere well the good shype God be our gyde’

TCD516.First Lines:
Ouer shyp is launched from the groundeBlessed be god both sane and
                    sownde…
TCD516.Last Lines:
…Whoo loue it not god make hym blyndeIn peynes to
                    abyde
